### FINDINGS

[F-006-01] Peck’s benchmark target is `revim`: known pass/fail cases against `acceptance-reviewer`, `code-reviewer`, and `planner`, with benchmark dirs defining agent + cases; `models.json` defines the model matrix. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/benchmarks/AGENTS.md:3`, `AGENTS.md:7`, `AGENTS.md:9-11`, `AGENTS.md:27-34`, `models.json:2-16`. Spec-kit: model-benchmark also has fixture/profile separation, selecting fixtures/executors/frameworks/scoring. `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/README.md:17`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/README.md:21-25`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: deep-improvement Lane B fixture/profile schema + reporter.

[F-006-02] Peck reviewer benchmarks are ground-truth verdict fixtures over real repo states/diffs: `config.sh` sets `CHECKOUT`, `INPUT`, `EXPECTED`; `run.sh` checks out/copies revim, runs the selected agent/model, extracts `Pass|Fail|Block`, and compares with expected. Peck: `revim-code-reviewer/config.sh:4-9`, `run.sh:32-45`, `run.sh:49-58`. Spec-kit currently has private-gold skill fixtures, but the scorer’s default Mode A measures routing/resource recall, not known-bug diff detection. `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:10-20`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs:388-408`. GAP: real. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: skill-benchmark scorer or new reviewer-fixture scorer.

[F-006-03] Peck planner uses an outcome oracle, not text-only judging: pass requires new commits, a `stories/*/story.md` diff, and clean tree. Peck: `revim-planner/README.md:13-16`, `revim-planner/config.sh:13-22`. Spec-kit model-benchmark has analogous executable/oracle scoring for code tasks via visible + hidden tests, but not planner/reviewer workflow-state oracles. `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/lib/code-task-scorer.cjs:300-312`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/lib/code-task-scorer.cjs:332-355`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: low. BLAST-RADIUS: Lane B scorer plugins, no need to change deep-research loops.

[F-006-04] Peck’s model sweep is simpler but directly comparable: one benchmark/case across many model aliases/variants and repeated runs, producing per-run reports and parallel summaries. Peck: `run-parallel.sh:2-5`, `run-parallel.sh:26-31`, `run-parallel.sh:44-50`, `run.sh:68-80`. Spec-kit already has a richer Cartesian sweep over models × variants × frameworks × fixtures × samples and rows keyed by model/executor/variant/framework/fixture. `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/sweep-benchmark.cjs:188-240`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/sweep-benchmark.cjs:444-471`. GAP: none for matrix mechanics. VERDICT: SKIP mechanics, ADAPT fixture oracle. EFFORT: S for mapping. RISK: low. BLAST-RADIUS: benchmark profiles only.

[F-006-05] Spec-kit can regression-test outputs in general, but not yet “reviewer prompt catches this known bug class” as a first-class benchmark: Lane B fixtures are pattern contracts or function code tasks, while Lane C default corpus validates skill routing/usefulness scenarios and D4 task outcome is advisory/opt-in. Spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/README.md:21-23`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-fixtures/README.md:17-28`, `.opencode/commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md:41-45`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:261-264`. Peck shows the missing shape: real diff/story input with expected pass/fail verdict. Peck: `revim-code-reviewer/config.sh:7-8`, `AGENTS.md:34`. GAP: real. VERDICT: ADOPT concept, ADAPT into spec-kit. EFFORT: M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: add reviewer-benchmark fixture type + expected verdict/finding rubric.

[F-006-06] Best mapping for a 006 reviewer-rule benchmark is Lane B model-benchmark with a new reviewer fixture/scorer, not pure Lane C router replay: the command is explicitly for model/prompt framework benchmarks with fixtures and pattern/5dim scoring, while skill-benchmark is primarily skill routing/discovery/usefulness. Spec-kit: `.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md:1-4`, `.opencode/commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md:6-9`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/README.md:69-100`. Peck: `run.sh:49-58`. GAP: real. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: Lane B profile schema, dispatcher prompt builder, scorer/report rows.

### RULED_OUT

- Not net-new: model alias/variant matrix and parallel repeated runs; spec-kit already expands models/variants/frameworks/fixtures/samples. Peck: `models.json:2-16`, `run-parallel.sh:26-31`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/sweep-benchmark.cjs:188-240`.
- Not net-new: hidden/withheld oracle concept; spec-kit code-task fixtures already use visible `tests` plus held-out `hidden_tests`. Spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-fixtures/README.md:17-28`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/lib/code-task-scorer.cjs:300-312`.
- Not sufficient as-is: Lane C private gold is routing/resource gold, not reviewer-bug verdict gold. Spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/skill-benchmark/fixtures/README.md:17-25`, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs:239-254`.

